USC - DTI ROI Summary Measures v2 + v3 (Mean)

Source: R/data.R
DTIROI_MEAN.Rd

USC - DTI ROI Summary Measures v2 + v3 (Mean) data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(DTIROI_MEAN)

Format

A data frame with 1750 observations and 310 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNIGO, ADNI4

  • COLPROT factor Study protocol of data collection , with levels: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • PTID character Participant ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID Range value: 11, ..., 10793

  • VISCODE character Visit code , with options: init, y2, y1, sc, y4, y3, 4_sc, 4_init, 4_m12

  • VISCODE2 character Translated visit code

  • EXAMDATE Examination Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • VERSION character Preprocessing pipeline version 2 = preprocessing pipeline as outlined in methods PDF: (USC - DTI ROI Summary Measures Methods v2 [ADNI3], date: 12/01/2021) ; 3 = preprocessing pipeline as outlined in methods PDF: (USC - DTI ROI Summary Measures Methods v3 [ADNI4], date: 04/02/2025) ; -4 = image was not processed as noted in QC column. Decoded Value: Yes

  • MANUFACTURER character Scanner Manufacturer , with options: Siemens, GE, Philips, SIEMENS, GE MEDICAL SYSTEMS

  • VOLUMES numeric Number of volumes prescribed by acquisition protocol Range value: 31, ..., 127

  • IMAGEUID numeric IMAGE ID of the raw diffusion scan Range value: 808826, ..., 11303224

  • DISTORTION_CORRECTION character In V3, EPI susceptibility distortion correction was run using a synthetic b0 (Synb0), b0s acquired with opposite phase encoding directions (APPA), or was completed in scanner (scanner), in addition to warping DWIs to T1w. In V2, susceptibility distortion was only corrected by warping DWIs to T1w (empty cells). Synb0=synthetic b0 ; APPA=b0s acquired with opposite phase encoding directions ; scanner=completed in scanner.

  • VOLUMES_AP numeric Number of volumes in the opposite phase encoding direction raw scan. Empty cell indicates there was no opposite phase encoding image provided to users on the IDA. Range value: 7, ..., 13

  • IMAGEUID_AP numeric IMAGE ID of the raw diffusion scan with an opposite phase encoding direction. Empty cell indicates there was no opposite phase encoding image provided to users on the IDA. Range value: 10248884, ..., 11297753

  • RUNDATE Processing Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • STATUS character Processing Completed , with options: complete, not processed

  • QC character Preprocessed DWI and scalar map quality check notes include: (1) a note if raw DWI were not processed due to incomplete acquisition (e.g., fewer volumes acquired than protocol), failed DICOM conversion, poor field of view (i.e., image cropped), or severe artifacts (e.g., motion, distortion); or (2) notes if preprocessed DWI had any remaining artifacts (e.g., motion, distortion, ghosting, hyperintensities in FA, etc.), pathology or anatomical anomalies, atlas registration failure, or if the voxel size differed from the prescribed acquisition protocol. These images should be used at own discretion.
